# Godot Engine Documentation Reference

## Critical Requirement
**ALWAYS** reference the official Godot Engine documentation when working with Godot-specific features, nodes, methods, or concepts. Use the most current documentation for Godot 4.x series.

## Documentation Sources
- **Primary**: https://docs.godotengine.org/en/stable/
- **API Reference**: https://docs.godotengine.org/en/stable/classes/
- **Tutorials**: https://docs.godotengine.org/en/stable/tutorials/
- **Community**: https://godotengine.org/community/

## When to Reference Documentation
- Node types and their properties (CharacterBody3D, Area3D, MeshInstance3D, etc.)
- Built-in methods (move_and_slide(), get_world_3d(), etc.)
- Physics and collision systems
- Shader programming and materials
- Animation systems
- Audio systems
- VR/XR implementation details
- Input handling
- Scene management

## Documentation Usage Pattern
When implementing or explaining Godot features:
1. First reference the official documentation
2. Provide the specific documentation link
3. Explain how it applies to the Phantom-Fray project
4. Include relevant code examples from the docs when helpful

## Project Context
This is a VR game project using Godot 4.5 with the godot-xr-tools plugin. Always ensure documentation references are compatible with Godot 4.x and consider VR-specific implementations.